00:15:46,403 --> 00:15:52,751
在另一边有一个姊妹要塞——拉法叶堡，也就是现在大桥布鲁克林侧塔楼所在地
and that was where the towers to the Brooklyn side of the bridge are now resting

292
00:15:55,350 --> 00:15:59,039
独立后，又过了一百年
after Independence there would still be another hundred years

293
00:15:59,039 --> 00:16:01,820
史坦顿岛才正式成为纽约市的一部分
before Staten Island was part of New York City

294
00:16:01,939 --> 00:16:06,719
在此期间，史坦顿岛诞生了科尼利厄斯·范德比尔特，
during this time Staten Island was a birthplace of Cornelius Vanderbilt

295
00:16:06,719 --> 00:16:10,287
他是这个新国家最早的白手起家的商业巨头之一
one of the first self-made tycoons in the new country

296
00:16:10,287 --> 00:16:15,047
通过控制和整合庞大的铁路及航运网络，
by controlling and consolidating large networks of railroads and shipping

297
00:16:15,047 --> 00:16:19,286
他在19世纪成为了世界上最富有的人之一
he became one of the wealthiest men in the world during the 1800s

298
00:16:19,285 --> 00:16:25,015
因为出生在史坦顿岛，很容易看出是什么引导他走向了那个方向：
and being from Staten Island it's easy to see what pointed him in that direction

299
00:16:25,015 --> 00:16:30,100
史坦顿岛作为一个岛屿，周围一直都有渡轮在运营
Staten Island being an island has always had faeries all the way around

300
00:16:36,699 --> 00:16:38,318
直到1880年代末铁路桥开通之前，
there were no Bridges until

301
00:16:38,318 --> 00:16:41,016
这里都没有桥梁连接
a railroad bridge opened up in the late 1880s

302
00:16:41,016 --> 00:16:47,877
曼哈顿、布鲁克林和新泽西一直是史坦顿岛农产品的市场
Manhattan Brooklyn and New Jersey were always the markets for Staten Island's Goods

303
00:16:47,877 --> 00:16:53,809
所以渡轮在史坦顿岛人的生活中一直扮演着至关重要的角色，
so the faeries were always playing a very important role in the lives of Staten Islanders

304
00:16:53,809 --> 00:16:56,075
因为这里曾是一个农业社区
because it was a farming Community

305
00:16:56,075 --> 00:17:04,244
这里一直是个农业社区，直到19世纪初，工业开始在北岸和东岸兴起，
it was an agricultural Community until the early 1800s when industry started popping up along the North Shore and the East Shore

306
00:17:04,244 --> 00:17:08,265
渡轮在接送人员往返方面非常重要，
so the faeries were important in bringing people back and forth

307
00:17:08,264 --> 00:17:10,179
尤其是对农民来说
but especially for the farmers

308
00:17:10,179 --> 00:17:13,784
范德比尔特年仅16岁时就创办了自己的渡轮公司，
when he was only 16 Vanderbilt started his own Ferry company

309
00:17:13,784 --> 00:17:19,312
后来他的儿子在尝试通过铁路将史坦顿岛与纽约连接起来方面发挥了重要作用
and later his son played a large role in trying to connect Staten Island to New York by rail

310
00:17:19,312 --> 00:17:23,918
我们在布鲁克林的视频中看过这张人口图表，我想再带大家看一遍
we looked at this population graph in the Brooklyn video but I want to look at it again

311
00:17:23,918 --> 00:17:29,282
你可以看到，虽然布鲁克林和曼哈顿的人口在这一百年里增长迅速，
you can see that while the population of Brooklyn and Manhattan grew quickly during these hundred years

312
00:17:29,282 --> 00:17:36,000
但史坦顿岛的增长缓慢，和其他区一样，因为它主要专注于农业 and 小型制造业
Staten Islands increased slowly along with the other Bros since it was primarily focused on Farming and small-scale Manufacturing

313
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:41,036
同样在此期间，这里的桑迪地（Sandy Ground）社区开始发展，
also during this time the neighborhood right here known as Sandy ground began to develop

314
00:17:41,036 --> 00:17:44,183
成为美国最早的自由黑人社区之一
as one of the earliest free black communities in the US

315
00:17:44,183 --> 00:17:48,066
荷兰人在纽约市地区蓄养了很多奴隶
the Dutch had a lot of slaves in the New York City area

316
00:17:48,066 --> 00:17:52,224
这是17世纪的一个事实，被认为是日常生活的一部分，
it's a matter of a fact of the 17th century it was considered daily life

317
00:17:52,224 --> 00:17:55,746
但我认为历史学家常因为它太丑陋而略过它
but it's one that I think historians gloss over cuz it's ugly

318
00:17:55,746 --> 00:18:01,297
在我看来，史坦顿岛上一直都有被奴役的人，
as far as I'm concerned there have been ens slaved people since on Staten Island

319
00:18:01,297 --> 00:18:04,835
甚至在建立永久定居点之前就有
you know before um before even permanent settlement

320
00:18:04,834 --> 00:18:08,459
尽管在1963年遭遇了大火，
despite being devastated by fire in 1963 Sandy ground

321
00:18:08,459 --> 00:18:12,905
桑迪地现在仍是最初创始人后代的家园
is still home to some of the descendants of its original Founders

322
00:18:12,905 --> 00:18:18,093
同样，因为史坦顿岛离市区相对较近，且有这些高低起伏的山丘，
also because Staten Island is relatively close to the city and has these big hilly Bluffs

323
00:18:18,093 --> 00:18:22,174
它成了富有的纽约人建造夏季度假房的热门地点
it became a popular spot for wealthy New Yorkers to build summer homes

324
00:18:22,174 --> 00:18:26,256
圣乔治地区的很多房子现在依然矗立着，
a lot of these houses are still standing in the St George area

325
00:18:26,256 --> 00:18:30,140
非常漂亮，拥有无敌的城市景观
and they're beautiful and have incredible views of the city

326
00:18:31,620 --> 00:18:36,719
这是我的两个问题的答案开始交织在一起的地方
this is where the answer to both of my questions starts to blend into one

327
00:18:36,799 --> 00:18:41,290
史坦顿岛成为纽约市的一部分之所以能被提上日程，
Staten and becoming part of the city of New York is only even on the table

328
00:18:41,290 --> 00:18:45,660
唯一的原因是史坦顿岛已经是纽约州的一部分了，我叫肯·戈尔德（Ken Gold）
because Staten is's already a part of New York State my name is Ken Gold

329
00:18:45,660 --> 00:18:49,464
我是一名美国城市教育历史学家
I'm a historian of American Urban education

330
00:18:49,464 --> 00:18:54,923
我一直在史坦顿岛学院任教，目前担任正教授，
I have been teaching at the College of Staten Island where I currently serve as a full professor

331
00:18:54,923 --> 00:18:58,563
也是2023年出版的《被遗忘的行政区》一书的作者
and I'm the author of the 2023 publication the Forgotten burough

332
00:18:58,563 --> 00:19:00,585
史坦顿岛就在地铁图上
stat is in the subway

333
00:19:02,304 --> 00:19:05,851
我们现在所知的城市边界是在1898年创建的，
the city boundary as we know it was created in 1898

334
00:19:05,851 --> 00:19:11,066
当时该地区所有的城市和城镇被合并为一个
when all of the cities and towns within the area were Consolidated into one

335
00:19:11,067 --> 00:19:17,573
合并之后，他们将县治（即政府所在地）搬到了渡轮旁的圣乔治，
and then after consolidation they moved the county seat which is the seat of government to St George

336
00:19:17,573 --> 00:19:20,826
因为那里靠近曼哈顿
by the ferry because of its proximity to Manhattan

337
00:19:20,826 --> 00:19:25,144
行政大楼（Borough Hall）就在这里，
this is where bro Hall is the first building that was pointed out to me after getting off the ferry

338
00:19:25,144 --> 00:19:25,188
这是我下渡轮后向我指出的第一栋建筑


339
00:19:25,188 --> 00:19:30,240
合并很大程度上是安德鲁·哈斯韦尔·格林（Andrew Haswell Green）努力的结果，
consolidation was largely the result of the efforts of Andrew Haswell green

340
00:19:30,240 --> 00:19:37,043
他希望创建一个统一的政府实体来管理整个港口
who wanted to create a single governmental entity that would control the harbor In Our Lifetime right

341
00:19:37,043 --> 00:19:41,878
在我们的有生之年，对吧？自由市场常被标榜为效率的保障，
free markets get presented as uh the mechanism for efficiency

342
00:19:41,878 --> 00:19:48,853
而公共部门则被描述为臃肿、低效的实体
and sort of the public sector gets you know presented as this bloated inefficient entity

343
00:19:48,854 --> 00:19:53,525
但120年前，安德鲁·哈斯韦尔·格林的观点恰恰相反
um but 120 years ago Andrew haswell's greens was exactly the opposite

344
00:19:53,525 --> 00:19:57,548
他的地理视角是整个纽约港
his Geographic vantage point was the harbor of New York City

345
00:19:57,549 --> 00:20:01,836
如果那是你的视角，如果你观察那个港口，
and if you that's your Vantage Point uh and you look at the harbor

346
00:20:01,836 --> 00:20:08,331
那么港口的入口就是纳罗斯海峡，而史坦顿岛就守在那个入口
then the entrance of that Harbor right is the ver the narrow straet and Staton lies at that entrance

347
00:20:08,331 --> 00:20:13,722
这就是为什么他总是把史坦顿岛包含在他的纽约合并提案中，
and that's why he always included it in his uh proposal to consolidate New York

348
00:20:13,722 --> 00:20:21,024
并且在一度有一些曼哈顿人推动将其排除在外时，他据理力争将其保留下来
and fought to keep it when uh at one point there were some manhattanites who were pushing for its exclusion

349
00:20:21,024 --> 00:20:25,155
史坦顿岛人期望加入城市后能获得很多好处
Staten Islanders expected a lot of benefits from joining the city

350
00:20:25,155 --> 00:20:27,931
我认为史坦顿岛的人民投票决定
I think the the people of Staten Island voted

351
00:20:27,931 --> 00:20:30,275
成为纽约市的一部分，
to become part of the city of New York

352
00:20:30,275 --> 00:20:33,113
是因为他们期望城市
because they expected that the city would help

353
00:20:33,112 --> 00:20:34,963
能帮助这个区进步和改善
the burrow advance and improve

354
00:20:34,963 --> 00:20:36,527
史坦顿岛希望
st9 was hoping that

355
00:20:36,527 --> 00:20:38,502
作为纽约市的一部分，
as part of New York City

356
00:20:38,502 --> 00:20:41,712
能获得大量的市政资金
they would get a lot of Municipal funds

357
00:20:41,712 --> 00:20:44,099
用于下水道、道路等基础设施建设
for sewers roads and the like

358
00:20:44,779 --> 00:20:49,091
你可以看到合并后不久皇后区和布朗克斯区的增长
you can see the growth of queens and the Bronx shortly after consolidation

359
00:20:49,092 --> 00:20:52,022
它们都享受到了成为城市一部分
they both enjoyed the benefits of being part of the city

360
00:20:52,022 --> 00:20:54,062
以及与地铁系统连接带来的好处
and being linked with the subway system

361
00:20:54,062 --> 00:20:57,199
但史坦顿岛从未连接到地铁
but Staten Island was never connected to the subway

362
00:20:57,199 --> 00:20:59,999
你知道，这导致了某种程度的孤立
you know it leads to kind of of a level of isolation

363
00:20:59,999 --> 00:21:02,681
在经济发展方面是经济孤立，
right the city you know it's economic isolation

364
00:21:02,681 --> 00:21:04,735
搬到这里的人变少了，
in terms of its Economic Development

365
00:21:04,735 --> 00:21:06,903
也是文化孤立
it's you know fewer people moving here

366
00:21:06,903 --> 00:21:08,215
也是文化孤立
it's cultural isolation

367
00:21:08,215 --> 00:21:11,614
我总是很惊讶，
I'm always amazed at how many students I've taught

368
00:21:11,614 --> 00:21:14,742
我教过的学生中有多少人竟然从未去过曼哈顿
that I teach that have never been to Manhattan

369
00:21:14,741 --> 00:21:17,290
我们在今天的地铁图上看到的唯一一条线，
the one line we see on today's subway map

370
00:21:17,290 --> 00:21:20,274
其实是比地铁早50年建造的一条铁路线
was a rail line built 50 years before the subway

371
00:21:20,274 --> 00:21:23,603
史坦顿岛比其他区更远，
Staten is further than the other buus

372
00:21:23,603 --> 00:21:25,582
所以我不认为
and so I I don't think

373
00:21:25,582 --> 00:21:29,361
它的人口会变得像皇后区
it would have become as populous as queens

374
00:21:29,360 --> 00:21:30,440
或布朗克斯区那么多
or the Bronx

375
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:34,170
但我认为它本来应该在几十年前就达到50万人口，
but I think it would have hit half a million decades ago

376
00:21:34,170 --> 00:21:36,701
而不是像现在这样还没完全达到
instead of still not quite being there

377
00:21:36,701 --> 00:21:41,194
让我感到震惊的是，
what's striking for me to learn about the development of Staten Island

378
00:21:41,194 --> 00:21:42,991
了解到史坦顿岛的发展其实是非常近期的事，
is just how recent it's been

379
00:21:42,991 --> 00:21:44,917
是的，我亲身经历过
yeah I mean I lived through it

380
00:21:44,917 --> 00:21:49,787
我亲历了史坦顿岛所谓的“农耕时期”
I I lived through the the so-called farming period on Staten Island

381
00:21:49,787 --> 00:21:54,157
当我79年搬到这里时，还有经营中的农场
when I moved here in 79 there was an active farm

382
00:21:54,157 --> 00:21:56,542
当我开车去朋友家时，
and as I was driving to a friend's house

383
00:21:56,542 --> 00:21:59,523
我看到一群牛在史坦顿岛购物中心的草坪上吃草，
I saw a herd of cows grazing on the St Island Mall

384
00:21:59,523 --> 00:22:01,610
那可是1979年了
the grass of the mall as late as 79

385
00:22:01,610 --> 00:22:05,018
史坦顿岛依然是目前为止最像农村的行政区
Staten Island is still easily the most rural burrow

386
00:22:05,018 --> 00:22:07,100
我知道这是一个奇怪的衡量方式，
and I know this is a weird way to measure it

387
00:22:07,100 --> 00:22:09,135
但当我在谷歌地图上闲逛时，
but when I was poking around on Google Maps

388
00:22:09,136 --> 00:22:10,934
我总能看到这些游泳池
I kept seeing all these swimming pools

389
00:22:10,933 --> 00:22:13,443
于是我查了一下，发现了这张地图
so I looked it up and I found this map

390
00:22:13,443 --> 00:22:15,469
史坦顿岛是一个明显的离群值
Staten Island is a clear outlier

391
00:22:15,470 --> 00:22:17,300
看看这些地上泳池
look at all of these ground pools

392
00:22:17,300 --> 00:22:20,071
显然这可能有多种原因，
obviously there could be multiple reasons for this

393
00:22:20,071 --> 00:22:22,288
但有空间去做这件事，
but the fact that there's space to do it

394
00:22:22,288 --> 00:22:23,507
我觉得说明了一些问题
I think says something

395
00:22:23,507 --> 00:22:27,593
尽管未开发的地貌标志着它与城市其他部分的距离，
although the undeveloped landscape marked its distance from the rest of the city

396
00:22:27,593 --> 00:22:30,760
但这同时也成了史坦顿岛人的骄傲
it also became a point point of Pride for the Staten Islanders

397
00:22:30,799 --> 00:22:34,527
这里感觉像是一个绿意盎然的小镇社区，
it felt like a small neighborhood town with a lot of greenery

398
00:22:34,527 --> 00:22:38,744
如果你见过1960年代的特拉维斯和托滕维尔镇，
if you ever saw the towns of Travis and Tottenville back in the 1960s

399
00:22:38,743 --> 00:22:41,799
你会以为自己身处中西部
you would have thought you were out in the midwest

400
00:22:41,799 --> 00:22:44,444
保护这些景观的努力催生了绿带（Green Belt），
efforts to preserve this led to the green belt

401
00:22:44,444 --> 00:22:47,261
即岛中心这片巨大的绿色区域
this large green area in the center of the island

402
00:22:47,261 --> 00:22:50,226
我想指出这片自然保护区中心
and I want to point out an interesting landmark

403
00:22:50,226 --> 00:22:52,560
的一个有趣的标志性建筑
in the center of this Nature Preserve

404
00:22:52,560 --> 00:22:54,781
这是海景医院（Sea View Hospital）旧址，
this is the site of C viw Hospital

405
00:22:54,781 --> 00:22:57,524
曾是全国最大的结核病疗养机构
the nation's largest tuberculosis facility

406
00:22:57,523 --> 00:23:00,208
它专门建在这里，
and it was spefic specifically built here

407
00:23:00,208 --> 00:23:05,053
是因为当时人们认为治疗结核病的方法是阳光和新鲜空气
because the cure to tuberculosis was believed to be sunshine and fresh air

408
00:23:05,054 --> 00:23:06,502
你住在这里，地势这么高，
you're up to here this high

409
00:23:06,502 --> 00:23:09,720
你会得到大量的新鲜空气和阳光
you're going to get a lot of fresh air and a lot of sunshine

410
00:23:09,719 --> 00:23:12,991
最初建了八栋医院大楼，
and originally there were eight hospitals buildings built

411
00:23:12,991 --> 00:23:14,656
四栋女用，四栋男用，
four for female four for male

412
00:23:14,656 --> 00:23:15,862
这很有意思
which was interesting

413
00:23:15,862 --> 00:23:17,848
在那个年代，他们实行男女隔离
they segregated the sexes in those days

414
00:23:17,848 --> 00:23:20,139
我们说的是1910年、1911年左右
we talking about 1910 1911

415
00:23:20,139 --> 00:23:23,653
因为我们处在城市中一个非常偏僻的地方，
since we're in a very isolated a part of the city

416
00:23:23,653 --> 00:23:26,952
周围没有太多给员工住的房子，
there weren't many housing out there for staff

417
00:23:26,952 --> 00:23:30,394
所以大多数员工就住在这个院区里
so most of staff lived right here on this campus

418
00:23:30,394 --> 00:23:36,186
这个设施的历史超级有趣，也相当阴森，
the history of this facility is super interesting and pretty creepy

419
00:23:36,186 --> 00:23:37,915
哇，吓到我了
whoa that spooked me

420
00:23:39,196 --> 00:23:41,577
是道，我还没准备好
yeah I know I wasn't ready for that

421
00:23:41,577 --> 00:23:44,086
但这是当初的一个原始担架
but this is one of the original gurns

422
00:23:44,086 --> 00:23:49,316
这是结核病时期他们使用的一些工具的展示
this is uh a display of some of the tools they used during the tuberculosis days

423
00:23:49,316 --> 00:23:52,599
看看这个锯子，这是用来锯骨头的
I mean look at this soore this was used to cut bone

424
00:23:52,799 --> 00:23:54,177
他们曾经还有一个胎儿标本
they also had a fetus once

425
00:23:54,177 --> 00:23:55,616
那个已经不在这里了，
that is no longer here

426
00:23:55,616 --> 00:23:58,233
因为那让人们感到不安，总之
cuz that was getting people upset anyway

427
00:23:58,233 --> 00:24:01,075
总之，缺乏地铁开始解释了
anyway the lack of Subway begins to explain

428
00:24:01,075 --> 00:24:03,520
这里为什么是“被遗忘的行政区”
the reason this was the Forgotten bur

429
00:24:03,520 --> 00:24:06,375
但还有另外两个主要原因，
but there's a couple other major reasons

430
00:24:06,375 --> 00:24:09,230
我给你们三秒钟猜猜谁该为此负责：
and I'll give you three seconds to guess

431
00:24:09,231 --> 00:24:12,015
罗伯特·摩西（Robert Moses）
